dence about violence=2C peace=2C and human nature (https://www.brainpickin=
gs.org/2014/08/21/leo-tolstoy-gandhi-letter-to-a-hindu/?mc_cid=3D584266f28=
3&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) is strewn with echoes of Thoreau)=2C and informed Ma=
rtin Luther King=2C Jr.=E2=80=99s ideals of nonviolent resistance (https:/=
/www.brainpickings.org/2015/03/18/martin-luther-king-letter-from-birmingha=
m-city-jail/?mc_cid=3D584266f283&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) .

More than half a century before women got the right to vote =E2=80=94 an e=
ra predating =E2=80=9Cthe invention of women=2C=E2=80=9D (https://www.brai=
npickings.org/2014/10/17/ursula-k-le-guin-gender/?mc_cid=3D584266f283&mc_e=
id=3D[UNIQID]) when =E2=80=9Cman=E2=80=9D actually meant man =E2=80=94 Th=
oreau writes:

Let every man make known what kind of government would command his respect=
=2C and that will be one step toward obtaining it.

After all=2C the practical reason why=2C when the power is once in the han=
ds of the people=2C a majority are permitted=2C and for a long period cont=
inue=2C to rule is not because they are most likely to be in the right=2C=
 nor because this seems fairest to the minority=2C but because they are ph=
ysically the strongest. But a government in which the majority rule in all=
 cases can not be based on justice=E2=80=A6 Can there not be a government=
 in which the majorities do not virtually decide right and wrong=2C but co=
nscience? =E2=80=A6 Must the citizen ever for a moment=2C or in the least=
 degree=2C resign his conscience to the legislator? Why has every man a co=
nscience then? I think that we should be men first=2C and subjects afterwa=
rd. It is not desirable to cultivate a respect for the law=2C so much as f=
or the right. The only obligation which I have a right to assume is to do=
 at any time what I think right. It is truly enough said that a corporatio=
n has no conscience; but a corporation of conscientious men is a
corporation with a conscience. Law never made men a whit more just; and=2C=
 by means of their respect for it=2C even the well-disposed are daily made=
 the agents on injustice.

In a sentiment of acute timeliness as we are called to confront (http://ww=
w.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/081298496X/bpnl-20?mc_cid=3D584266f283&mc_ei=
d=3D[UNIQID]) the atrocities of today=E2=80=99s criminal justice system a=
nd the systemic injustices of mass incarceration=2C Thoreau adds:

Under a government which imprisons unjustly=2C the true place for a just m=
an is also a prison.

To the intuitive outcry of what is to be done=2C which bellows from deep i=
n the soul of any human being who has managed to stay woke (https://twitte=
r.com/wendymac/status/752209385498169344?mc_cid=3D584266f283&mc_eid=3D[UN=
IQID]) =2C Thoreau answers:

Cast your whole vote=2C not a strip of paper merely=2C but your whole infl=
uence. A minority is powerless while it conforms to the majority; it is no=
t even a minority then; but it is irresistible when it clogs by its whole=
 weight. If the alternative is to keep all just men in prison=2C or give u=
p war and slavery=2C the State will not hesitate which to choose. If a tho=
usand men were not to pay their tax bills this year=2C that would not be a=
 violent and bloody measure=2C as it would be to pay them=2C and enable th=
e State to commit violence and shed innocent blood. This is=2C in fact=2C=
 the definition of a peaceable revolution=2C if any such is possible.

Civil Disobedience (http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0143106503/bpnl=
-20?mc_cid=3D584266f283&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) is an indispensable read for e=
very democratically minded=2C socially conscious human being awake to just=
ice. Complement it with Walt Whitman on how literature bolsters democracy=
 (https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/02/24/walt-whitman-democratic-vistas/=
?mc_cid=3D584266f283&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C Eleanor Roosevelt on our indi=
vidual responsibility in social change (https://www.brainpickings.org/2016=
/05/02/eleanor-roosevelt-tomorrow-is-now/?mc_cid=3D584266f283&mc_eid=3D[U=
NIQID]) =2C and James Baldwin on freedom and how we imprison ourselves (ht=
tps://www.brainpickings.org/2016/05/09/james-baldwin-freedom/?mc_cid=3D584=
